[node name="Terminal" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]TERMINAL COMMANDS[/color][/b]
The terminal is your primary tool for network-level response.

[b]Commands:[/b]
• [color=yellow]help[/color] - Lists all available commands.
• [color=yellow]scan [hostname][/color] - Performs a security scan on the target host. Required to confirm infection before isolation.
• [color=yellow]isolate [hostname][/color] - Disconnects the target host from the corporate network. Use this to contain active malware or exfiltration.
• [color=yellow]status[/color] - Displays the current terminal status and your active ticket.

[b]Note:[/b] Incorrect use of 'isolate' on critical infrastructure (like Servers) may trigger service outages and lead to a [color=red]Terminal Lockout[/color]."
metadata/_tab_index = 0

[node name="SIEM" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
visible = false
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]SIEM LOG VIEWER[/color][/b]
The SIEM (Security Information and Event Management) aggregates logs from across the organization.

[b]Usage:[/b]
• [b]Investigation:[/b] Click on a log entry to view detailed metadata (IPs, Hostnames, Messages).
• [b]Evidence:[/b] To solve a ticket with 'Compliant' status, you must attach the required logs as evidence.
• [b]How to Attach:[/b] Select a log, choose the relevant ticket from the dropdown, and click [b]Attach Evidence[/b].

[b]Filtering:[/b]
Use the filter buttons (Security, High Severity) to narrow down thousands of entries to find the 'smoking gun' for your incident."
metadata/_tab_index = 1

[node name="Email" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
visible = false
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]EMAIL ANALYZER[/color][/b]
Most breaches start with a single email. Analyze carefully before acting.

[b]Key Indicators:[/b]
• [b]Spoofing:[/b] Check if the 'From' address matches the expected internal domain.
• [b]Malicious Links:[/b] Hover over or scan links to check for suspicious domains or phishing redirects.
• [b]Attachments:[/b] Scan all attachments for malware signatures.

[b]Actions:[/b]
• [color=red]Quarantine[/color]: Use when you are certain the email is malicious.
• [color=green]Approve[/color]: Use for legitimate business communication.

[i]Warning: Misidentifying a legitimate executive email as phishing will cause reputation loss.[/i]"
metadata/_tab_index = 2

[node name="Procedures" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Panel/VBox/Content/TabContainer"]
visible = false
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "[b][color=cyan]INCIDENT RESPONSE PROCEDURES[/color][/b]

[b]Resolution Strategies:[/b]
• [b]Compliant:[/b] The standard operating procedure. Requires all evidence (logs) to be attached. No risk of missing hidden consequences.
• [b]Efficient:[/b] Priority is speed. No evidence required, but high risk of missing 'Hidden Risks' that cause later breaches.
• [b]Emergency:[/b] Immediate resolution for catastrophic events. Use only when time is critical.

[b]Analyst Archetypes:[/b]
Your performance determines your reputation:
• [b]By-the-Book:[/b] High compliance, slow but safe.
• [b]Cowboy:[/b] High efficiency, fast but dangerous.
• [b]Negligent:[/b] Letting alerts time out."
metadata/_tab_index = 3
